claim.claim-text:
A double-sided integrated bearing sleeve (100) adapted to operate in flow meters, comprising the following axially connected to each other:
- a lower part (110) in the shape of a ring, with a lower inlet-outlet (111), adapted for radial bearing of a first axle (201);
- a central part (120) in the shape of two rings axially connected to each other, comprising
at least two symmetrical lateral inlets-outlets (121),
a cylindrical thrust bearing (122) adapted to simultaneously bearing the first axle (201) and a second axle (202);
- an upper part (130) in the shape of a ring, smaller in diameter than the lower part (110), comprising an upper inlet-outlet (131), adapted for radial bearing of the second axle (202).

The bearing system (200), comprising:
- the bearing sleeve (100) according to any one of claims 1 to 7;
- the first axle (201), adapted to be seated with its first end in the lower part (110) of the bearing sleeve (100);
- the second axle (202), adapted to be seated with its first end in the upper part (130) of the bearing sleeve (100);

A double-sided monolithic bearing sleeve (100) for connecting to the rotor of flow meters, comprising
- a lower part (110) in the shape of a ring, with a lower inlet-outlet (111), adapted for radial bearing of a first axle (201);
- a central part (120) in the shape of two concentric rings , comprising
at least two symmetrical radially positioned inlets-outlets (121),
a cylindrical thrust bearing (122) adapted to simultaneously bearing the first axle (201) and a second axle (202);
- an upper part (130) in the shape of a ring, smaller in diameter than the lower part (110), comprising an upper inlet-outlet (131), adapted for radial bearing of the second axle (202).

A bearing system (200), comprising:
- the bearing sleeve (100) according to any one of claims 1 to 7;
- the first axle (201), adapted to be seated with its first end in the lower part (110) of the bearing sleeve (100);
- the second axle (202), adapted to be seated with its first end in the upper part (130) of the bearing sleeve (100);
